<p class="p">Water flux amongst various soil layers due to HR through the root conduit was followed by Ryel et al. [
 <xref rid="pone.0183071.ref015" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">15</xref>] and Lee et al. [
 <xref rid="pone.0183071.ref030" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">30</xref>], which can be formulated as: 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0183071.e005" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0183071.e005.jpg" id="pone.0183071.e005g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M5" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">H</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">j</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">C</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">T</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mstyle displaystyle="false" class="mstyle">
      <msubsup class="msubsup">
       <mo class="mo">∑</mo>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">j</mi>
        <mo class="mo">=</mo>
        <mn class="mn">1</mn>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">n</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msubsup>
     </mstyle>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">φ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">j</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo class="mo">−</mo>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">φ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">i</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">m</mi>
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">a</mi>
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">x</mi>
    <mo class="mo">⁡</mo>
    <mo class="mo">(</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mtext class="mtext">c</mtext>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mtext class="mtext">i</mtext>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">,</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">j</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">)</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">f</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">r</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">o</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">o</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">t</mi>
        <mo class="mo">,</mo>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">i</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">f</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">r</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">o</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">o</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">t</mi>
        <mo class="mo">,</mo>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">j</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
      <mo class="mo">−</mo>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">f</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">r</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">o</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">o</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">t</mi>
        <mo class="mo">,</mo>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">x</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">δ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">T</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(5)</label>
 </disp-formula> where C
 <sub class="sub">RT</sub> is the maximum radial soil-root conductance of the entire active root system with a constant value of 0.097 (cm/Mpa/h) [
 <xref rid="pone.0183071.ref015" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">15</xref>]; n is the number of soil layers; φ
 <sub class="sub">i</sub> and φ
 <sub class="sub">j</sub> are the soil water potential within the ith and jth soil layer, respectively; f
 <sub class="sub">root,i</sub> and f
 <sub class="sub">root,j</sub> are the root fraction within the ith and jth soil layer, respectively; f
 <sub class="sub">root,x</sub> = f
 <sub class="sub">root,j</sub> when the soil water content within the j layer is larger than it is within the i layer, or f
 <sub class="sub">root,x</sub> = f
 <sub class="sub">root,i</sub> otherwise; and δ
 <sub class="sub">T</sub> is a switch controlling HR, which is generally only valid at night, that is equal to 0 during the day and 1 at night. The relative soil-root conductance for water within ith (c
 <sub class="sub">i</sub>) or jth (c
 <sub class="sub">j</sub>) soil layer, is calculated using the following empirical relationship: 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0183071.e006" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0183071.e006.jpg" id="pone.0183071.e006g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M6" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mtext class="mtext">c</mtext>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mtext class="mtext">i</mtext>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msup class="msup">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mn class="mn">1</mn>
        <mo class="mo">+</mo>
        <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
        <mfrac class="mfrac">
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <msub class="msub">
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">φ</mi>
           </mrow>
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi class="mi">i</mi>
           </mrow>
          </msub>
         </mrow>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <msub class="msub">
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">φ</mi>
           </mrow>
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mn class="mn">50</mn>
           </mrow>
          </msub>
         </mrow>
        </mfrac>
        <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">b</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msup>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(6)</label>
 </disp-formula> where φ
 <sub class="sub">50</sub> is the soil water potential when the soil hydraulic conductance is reduced by 50%, and b is an empirical constant.
</p>
